text: Doniaga () is a small village in De Fryske Marren municipality in the province Friesland of the Netherlands and has around 100 citizens (2017).Kerncijfers wijken en buurten 2017 - CBS It is located west of the Tjeukemeer and named after the Donia family. ==History== Before 2009, Doniaga was part of the Skarsterlân municipality and before 1984 it was part of Doniawerstal. ==References== ==External links== Category:De Fryske Marren Category:Populated places in Friesland
title: Doniaga
